-- Incheon May Invest in Russia Far East Airports, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2012-09-14T04:25:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-14/incheon-may-invest-in-russia-far-east-airports-vedomosti-says.html
South Korea’s Incheon International
Airport Corp. may gain a blocking stake in an airport holding
company focused on  Russia ’s Far East in partnership with the
Khabarovsk airport,  Vedomosti said , citing Konstantin Basyuk,
board chairman of the Khabarovsk, Russia airport.  The venture wants to buy Russian airports in Petropavlovsk-
Kamchatka, Magadan, Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk and may be awarded other
airports by the state, Vedomosti said, citing a presentation
from the airport.  Seoul airport already owns 10 percent of the Khabarovsk
airport, Vedomosti said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow at 
